Uses of Package
org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge

  • Packages that use org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge 
    Package Description
    org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge
    Classes for Generic protocol-independent interactions to IO-homecontrolled devices via the Velux gateway.
    org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.json
    JSON-protocol specific implementations of the interactions to IO-homecontrolled devices.
    org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip
    SLIP-protocol specific implementations of the interactions to IO-homecontrolled devices.
    org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip.io
    SLIP-protocol I/O with the bridge.
    org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.handler
    Classes for handling any kind of openHAB events and requests, providing a synchronisation between openHAB and the real world.
  • Classes in org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge used by org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge 
    Class and Description
    VeluxBridge
    2nd Level I/O interface towards the Velux bridge.
    VeluxBridgeActuators.Channel
    Actuator information consisting of: isRetrieved (boolean), existingProducts (VeluxExistingProducts).
    VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel
    Bridge information consisting of: VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel.isRetrieved describing the retrieval state, VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel.gwState containing the brief gateway state, VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel.gwStateDescription containing the verbose gateway state.
    VeluxBridgeGetFirmware.Channel
    Bridge information consisting of: isRetrieved (boolean flag), firmwareVersion (human readable String).
    VeluxBridgeInstance
    This interface is implemented by classes that deal with a specific Velux bridge and its configuration.
    VeluxBridgeLANConfig.Channel
    IP Network configuration, consisting of: isRetrieved (boolean flag), ipAddress, subnetMask, defaultGW and enabledDHCP.
    VeluxBridgeScenes.Channel
    Actuator information consisting of: existingScenes (VeluxExistingScenes).
    VeluxBridgeWLANConfig.Channel
    Wireless network configuration, consisting of: isRetrieved, wlanSSID, wlanPassword.

    Class and Description
    VeluxBridge
    2nd Level I/O interface towards the Velux bridge.
    VeluxBridgeActuators
    The VeluxBridgeActuators represents a complete set of transactions for retrieving of any available products into a structure VeluxBridgeActuators.channel defined on the Velux bridge.
    VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel
    Bridge information consisting of: VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel.isRetrieved describing the retrieval state, VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel.gwState containing the brief gateway state, VeluxBridgeDeviceStatus.Channel.gwStateDescription containing the verbose gateway state.
    VeluxBridgeGetFirmware.Channel

    VeluxBridgeLANConfig.Channel
    IP Network configuration, consisting of: isRetrieved (boolean flag), ipAddress, subnetMask, defaultGW and enabledDHCP.
    VeluxBridgeProvider
    This interface is implemented by classes that provide general communication with the Velux bridge.
    VeluxBridgeScenes
    The VeluxBridgeScenes represents a complete set of transactions for retrieving of any available scenes into a structure VeluxExistingScenes defined on the Velux bridge.
    VeluxBridgeWLANConfig.Channel
    Wireless network configuration, consisting of: isRetrieved, wlanSSID, wlanPassword.
